On January 31, 2017, a ceremony was held to welcome Elaine Chao as the new Secretary of the Department of Transportation. The event was attended by her husband, Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell, as well as her father, Dr. James Chao. Chao has previously served as Secretary of Labor under President George W. Bush and has held various positions in the private sector and government. She brings a wealth of experience to her new role and is expected to oversee significant investments in the nation's infrastructure. Vice President Mike Pence expressed his gratitude for Chao's willingness to serve the country once again and expressed confidence in her ability to make America great again.